hopobject.body: A few months innovation-in-healthcare.pl Scientists have little doubt that human-induced global warming is overwhelmingly responsible; studies suggest that only between 5 per cent and 30 per cent of the decline over the past 30 years could be due to natural weather cycles. Indeed some years, like 2009 and 2010, when these cycles should have resulted in lots of sea ice, are among those when it has been at its scarcest.
